# Plan Mode Checklist

Every plan produced by the CreatePlan tool MUST include the following top-level sections, in this exact wording so tooling can verify them. Use "N/A: <one-line reason>" if a section truly doesn't apply.

- `## Tests` — see [.cursor/rules/plan-requires-tests.mdc](.cursor/rules/plan-requires-tests.mdc)
- `## Metrics` — see [.cursor/rules/plan-requires-metrics-logging.mdc](.cursor/rules/plan-requires-metrics-logging.mdc)
- `## Logging` — see [.cursor/rules/plan-requires-metrics-logging.mdc](.cursor/rules/plan-requires-metrics-logging.mdc)
- `## Documentation` — see [.cursor/rules/update-docs-on-design.mdc](.cursor/rules/update-docs-on-design.mdc)
- `## UI/UX` — see [.cursor/rules/plan-requires-ui-ux.mdc](.cursor/rules/plan-requires-ui-ux.mdc)

## Workflow

1. **Before drafting**: read every `alwaysApply: true` rule under `.cursor/rules/` even if not yet attached as inline content. Use Glob + Read.
2. **While drafting**: include the five sections above; defer none of them to follow-ups.
3. **After CreatePlan**: a hook checks the plan body for the required headers and emits a warning if any are missing. Treat the warning as a hard error — fix the plan immediately.
